CSS.Explanation:
To center text in CSS, use the text-align property and define it with the value “center.”
Eg * {
text-align: center;
}

The declaration block contains one or more declarations separated by semicolons.

Each declaration includes a CSS property name and a value, separated by a colon.
Multiple CSS declarations are separated with semicolons, and declaration blocks are surrounded by curly braces.

p {
  color: red;
  text-align: center;
}

JS.Explanation:
Functions can be created in different ways:
A function as a statement. Eg, function functionName (parameters) 

A function as an expression. Eg, functionName([parameters]) {
   statements
} 
A function as an arrow function. Eg,  let myFunc = () =>{}

Use if to specify a block of code to be executed, if a specified condition is true. 
The syntax is 
if (condition) {
  //  block of code to be executed if the condition is true
}

The for loop has the following syntax:
for (statement 1; statement 2; statement 3) {
// code block to be executed
}

The while loop loops through a block of code as long as a specified condition is true.
It's syntax is:
while (condition) {
  // code block to be executed
}

You can assign a value to a variable using equal to (=) operator when you declare it or before using it.
Eg:
var <variable-name>;
var <variable-name> = <value>;
